The researchers say that the findings could help dog owners, veterinarians, and trainers to better understand their pet's emotions.
John Bradshaw, an expert in dog behaviour and visiting fellow at the University of Bristol's Faculty of Veterinary Medicine, said this was not the first study to examine whether left and right are important for dogs.
