For what is there to be lacking in a person who regularly throws his fast-food bags out of the car window?!
Especially on weekends, discarded paper bags are found on roadsides and in car parks.
"Why?" I ask myself.
Are people too dumb to take the bags home or to the next garbage can?
It's not just that the paperwork is messing up the landscape.
Bags have also covered roadway structures such as guardrails, causing accidents.
The "throwaway society" does not think about such things, and probably does not even know what the word means.
If you are often out at night, especially with several people in the car, you know what a back seat can look like after a night of partying: clothing, bottles, and other trash piles up.
